INTRODUCTION: Frailty is considered as an early stage of disability which, 
differently from disability, is still amenable for preventive interventions and 
is reversible. In 2011, the "Geriatric Frailty Clinic (G.F.C) for Assessment of 
Frailty and Prevention of Disability" was created in Toulouse, France, in 
association with the University Department of General Medicine and the 
Midi-Pyrénées Regional Health Authority. This structure aims to support the 
